      narr:aboutNode narr:Narrative_UseCase2AgenticSteering ;
      narr:hasConvictionLevel narr:Conviction_Boulder ;
      narr:supports narr:Narrative_UseCase2AgenticSteering .

    narr:Claim_UseCase3MethodologyLayer a narr:Claim ;
      dct:source narr:Sample_SteeringDecisionProcess_May2026 ;
      skos:note "Use Case 3 is the methodology layer — the shared process underneath many engagements, extracted and aligned so one memory substrate serves every team, human or agent. It addresses the commonalities across different engagements, different clients, different processes. This is distinct from Use Cases 1 and 2 in that the 'team being steered' is the shared process itself, not a specific human team or agent." ;
      narr:aboutNode narr:Narrative_UseCase3SharedProcessSteering ;
      narr:hasConvictionLevel narr:Conviction_Boulder ;
      narr:supports narr:Narrative_UseCase3SharedProcessSteering .

    narr:Claim_AswrittenNeverTheLoop a narr:Claim ;
      dct:source narr:Sample_SteeringDecisionProcess_May2026 ;
      skos:note "In every use case, aswritten is the memory the steering runs on — never the tool that does the governing or orchestrating. This is a hard positioning constraint: aswritten is substrate, not loop. The loop may be a human governance process (Use Case 1), an agentic orchestration system (Use Case 2), or a methodology alignment process (Use Case 3)." ;
      narr:aboutNode narr:Narrative_AswrittenIsMemorySubstrate ;
      narr:hasConvictionLevel narr:Conviction_Foundation ;
      narr:supports narr:Narrative_AswrittenIsMemorySubstrate .

